# Documentation (ai-telegram-bot)

## Single source

- **All user-facing documentation** lives in **`README.md`** at the repo root.
- Use a **table of contents** at the top (links to `##` headings) for navigation.
- When behavior, configuration, or APIs change, update **`README.md`** in the same PR.

## Diagrams only under docs

- **`docs/diagrams/*.puml`** — PlantUML sources; link them from the **Diagrams** section of `README.md`.
- Do not reintroduce AsciiDoc/Markdown doc trees, Gradle doc plugins, or generate scripts unless the team explicitly opts back in.

## Style

- Prefer short tables and fenced `bash` / `http` blocks.
- No secrets in examples — use placeholders; point to **`config.example.env`**.
- Keep **module/architecture** notes brief in `README.md`; expand only when it helps operators.
